  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Can I change the nominee details in Atal Pension Yojana?",
  "response": "Yes, you can change the nominee details in your **Atal Pension Yojana (APY)** account. The nominee is the person who will receive the pension benefits in case of the subscriber's demise, so ensuring the nominee details are up to date is crucial.\n\nHere\u2019s how you can update the nominee details:\n\n### Steps to Change Nominee in Atal Pension Yojana:\n1. **Form Submission**:\n   - Visit the bank or post office where you have enrolled in the Atal Pension Yojana.\n   - Obtain and fill out the **APY Subscriber Details Update Form**. This form is specifically for updating subscriber details, including nominee information.\n\n2. **Provide Required Information**:\n   - Fill in the new nominee\u2019s details, such as name, relationship, date of birth, and share of the pension benefits.\n   - You can nominate more than one person and specify the percentage of the pension each nominee will receive.\n\n3. **Submit Documents**:\n   - Provide proof of identity and address (if required) for verification.\n   - The bank or post office may also ask for your APY account details for reference.\n\n4. **Verification**:\n   - The bank or post office will verify the details and update the nominee information in your APY account.\n\n5. **Acknowledgment**:\n   - Once the update is completed, you will receive an acknowledgment or confirmation from the bank or post office.\n\n### Important Points to Remember:\n- Ensure the nominee details are accurate and complete to avoid issues in the future.\n- You can update the nominee details at any time during the tenure of the APY account.\n- If you do not update the nominee, the pension benefits will be distributed as per the existing nominee details.\n\nIf you have any specific queries or face issues while updating the nominee, you can contact your bank or post office where the APY account is registered.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
